{
  "texts": [
    "The greater the incongruence between the person and the environment within each domain, the greater the likelihood the worker is experiencing burnout.",
    "In contrast, when high levels of fit are achieved, workers are more likely to be resilient to conditions of stress and engaged with their work (11).",
    "Identifying areas from this model in which conditions can be improved (i.e., low levels of fit) can lead to the development of strategies targeting issues at their source and effectively ameliorate burnout (10).",
    "To ensure congruence between data collection and the theoretical foundations of this study, the questions posed to participants were framed around the six Areas of Worklife to identify specific problem areas within each domain (Supplementary material).",
    "An intrinsic case study design was chosen for this study as this methodology is ideal for examining issues that are context-dependent, and allows the researcher to focus on the phenomenon of interest while being situated in a particular social and physical context (33, 34)."
  ]
}